## Features

### Core Features

**1. Multi-Format Ingestion**
- Upload PDF books of any size
- Ingest YouTube videos by URL (any video — no captions needed)
- Both can coexist in the same collection

**2. Hybrid Retrieval (BM25 + Semantic)**
- Semantic search: finds chunks by *meaning*, not just keywords
- BM25 (keyword): finds exact term matches
- Combined with 70% semantic / 30% keyword weighting
- Gets the best of both — neither alone is as accurate

**3. Dynamic Adaptive Chunking**
- Chunk size automatically scales with document size
  - Small docs (≤20 pages) → 500 token chunks, 60 overlap
  - Medium docs (≤60 pages) → 800 tokens, 100 overlap
  - Large docs (≤150 pages) → 1100 tokens, 140 overlap
  - Very large (150+ pages) → 1400 tokens, 180 overlap
- YouTube videos → 1200 token chunks with 150 overlap (preserves conversation flow)
- RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter respects paragraph and sentence boundaries

**4. Whisper AI Transcription for YouTube**
- Downloads audio using yt_dlp (works on any public video)
- Transcribes locally using faster-whisper (base model, CPU-friendly)
- Groups transcript into 2-minute "pages" with [MM:SS] timestamps
- Every answer from video content cites exact timestamps

**5. Page-Level Citations**
- Every answer shows which book and which page the information came from
- YouTube answers cite timestamps
- Relevance scores shown per source (0–100%)
- Click any source card to see the exact text chunk that was used

**6. Collection Management**
- Organize books into named collections (e.g. "psychology", "finance", "lectures")
- Create, switch, and delete collections independently
- Remove individual books without affecting the rest
- Re-uploading the same book safely replaces old data (no duplicates)

**7. Structured Answer Format**
LLaMA answers follow a fixed format:
- Title
- Overview (2–3 sentence summary)
- Key Points (bullet points with bold terms)
- Details (expanded prose with inline citations)
- Sources Used (list of books and pages)

**8. Book & Content-Type Filtering**
- Filter queries to a single specific book
- Filter by content type: PDFs only, YouTube only, or all
- Useful when you know which source has the answer

